  "description": [
    "THE BROWNINC CHIEF John E Davies Editor and Owner A weekly newspaper published every Friday at Browning Glacier County Montana Entered as 2nd class matter July 15 1931 at the postoffice at Browning Montana under act of March 3 1879 Subscription 200 year in advance KOREA IN PROSPECTIVE It is becoming increasingly evident that the future of Korea is not going to be quickly deter mined Neither negotiation nor fighting offers much prospect for an early settlement The truce talks appear stalled if not de funct and military action has taken the center of the stage Yet short of very much heavier investments of men and equip ment by one sideand not by the other neither appears likely soon to conquer the whole penin sula There is reason to believe that the aggression in Korea was in tended as the first step towards capture of Japan Such reason ing underscores the importance of the United Nations success in halting the Communists in Korea In that light the stalemate looks not only like a moral victory for world law however imperfectly expressed so far but like a vital holding action in the world pow er struggle It is possible of course"
  ],
